<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 02 at 6:28PM CDT until July 02 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS Bismarck</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 700 PM CDT
FOR WESTERN BURKE AND EAST CENTRAL DIVIDE COUNTIES...
At 627 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northeast of
Battleview, or 21 miles west of Bowbells, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Public.
IMPACT...Expect considerable tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings.
Locations impacted include...
Powers Lake, Lignite, Columbus, Flaxton and Larson.
THUNDERSTORM DAMAGE THREAT...CONSIDERABLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...OBSERVED
MAX WIND GUST...70 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
